This is the Deploy TCP proxy server. This daemon should run on an aTech Server
and provides the bridge between an aTech application and the agent running on
a customer's network.

## Installation

Check out this code onto a server and create the following configuration files.

* ca.pem - The CA certificate used to authenticate agents
* certificate.pem - The server certificate used to authenticate this server
* key.pem - The key corresponding to certificate.pem
* psk - A 40 character pre-shared key used to authenticate aTech client apps

Finally, execute server.rb
